<P N="2">II. God pleads his own and his people's cau&s;e, by <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> omnipotent, omni&s;cient, and omnipre&s;ent &s;pirit: <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 word"> &s;ets home his divine word upon the hearts of men; he removes their enmity again&s;t God and his people: he convinces and converts the unconverted; he &s;heds
